1.title: Bubba, Cody and Booger
1.plot: It's another busy week for the Alabama cowboys as Bubba races to get his house ready for his fiancée, Cody tries to carry on after selling his prized rodeo horse, and Booger mulls over a job offer in Texas that might be too good to refuse.

2.title: An American Tradition
2.plot: In this episode, the cowboys are called in to rustle up some calves in a very unusual location. Booger mentors a young boy. Cody is outgrowing his house. And Bubba is offered a job.

9.title: New Beginnings
9.plot: Bubba and Kaley welcome their baby girl into the world, Cody is given a week to complete a big contracting job for a local rancher, and Booger introduces his new girlfriend to his grandma. Finally, the whole gang gets to meet baby Andie.

2.title: Put A Ring On It
2.plot: Cody, Bubba and Booger act fast to stop the spread of an infection across the herd. Bubba is caught between his work family in Alabama and his family life in Mississippi. Cody and Misty invest in their future. Booger prepares to pop the question.

3.title: Tradition vs. Technology
3.plot: All work, no play is not the cowboy way. Bubba, Cody and Booger have an office to build, but find time for a best man competition and a modern game of hide-and-go-seek. Jaclyn seeks the perfect dress. Misty finds Cody with a sweet surprise.

4.title: Bulls on the Beach
4.plot: An easy job becomes risky business when the boys sort cattle. Torn between two worlds, Bubba trades saddles for spreadsheets. Cody seeks a sponsor to make Bulls on the Beach the biggest event yet. Booger gets swept off his feet with dance lessons.

6.title: Tying the Knot
6.plot: Booger and Jaclyn will finally say "I do" on an extra-special episode of The Cowboy Way! There won't be a dry eye in the house when the happy couple weds in a gorgeous Southern ceremony. Come join in the celebration as these newlyweds ride into their happily ever after!

7.title: All For One or One For Himself?
7.plot: Things are heating up on The Cowboy Way! Booger and Jaclyn have fun in the sun on their honeymoon, while in Alabama, Misty feels the pressure of running her new business. When the boys sit down to talk about the future of Faith Cattle Co., the conversation turns red hot! Can they work it out? Or will Faith Cattle Co. go up in flames?

8.title: Happy Trails
8.plot: On the season two finale of The Cowboy Way, the winds of change sweep our boys into the next chapter of their lives. Bubba mends fences with Cody and Booger, but reveals he's moving to Mississippi. Booger and Jaclyn say hello to their new future on Booger's ranch. And the boys give thanks to their gathered family and friends for supporting Faith Cattle Co. through the years.

1.title: My Heart's in Alabama
1.plot: The boys explore growing their cattle business in unexpected ways. Bubba is working for his father-in-law, but his heart's back in the saddle. Cody manages a rodeo and a steer mishap. Booger deals with his home getting a woman's touch. As the three cowboys sort yearlings, they devise a plan to elevate their cooking and their company.

2.title: There's No Place Like Home
2.plot: The stress of maintaining a long-distance relationship leads Bubba and Kaley to make a tough decision about their family's future. As the guys try to use their cowboy skills to open a steakhouse, they decide to get some on-the-job training by working a hectic dinner rush shift at a local eatery.

3.title: Man Down!
3.plot: Bubba's horse bucks and throws him on a bone-breaking fall that immobilizes his work with the cattle company. Misty gives Cody a surprise gift from the heart. The guys pitch each other competing cowboy ideas for their steakhouse, but only one of them has a vision with sizzle.

4.title: Filet of Dreams
4.plot: Bubba will try anything to help his aching back. Booger has Matthew for the day and draws on the bonding time he had with his own grandfather to make a special new memory. The cowboys put their steakhouse dreams on the line to recruit a business partner for their restaurant.

5.title: True Grits
5.plot: Bubba's back injury can't stop him from galloping ahead with making Andie's first birthday unforgettable with a secret surprise. Booger jumps at the chance to rebuild his family legacy by buying back his granddaddy's land, but will the sellers consider his lowball offer?

6.title: Man Up
6.plot: The cowboys team up to wrangle and pen dangerous long-horned cattle. Their steakhouse plans gallop ahead as they learn more about the restaurant biz by taking lessons from professionals. Bubba's feeling ready to get back in the saddle, but will his chiropractor finally give him the okay?

7.title: Horse of a Different Color
7.plot: The cowboys team up to get their new herd "feed-broke," but a stuck truck needs super-mom Kaley to save the day. Chef Bill gives his final verdict on the guys' pop-up restaurant. Booger teaches a young polo player about Western riding, but who's getting schooled when he's challenged to play polo?

8.title: Aged to Perfection

9.title: On a Mission
9.plot: In this new episode, the cowboys spend quality time with family to discuss their futures. Booger's horse clinic becomes a way to give back to the community. When the boys set up a mixer for bachelors Frankie and Hodge, speed-dating turns into a literal horse race to win the ladies' affections.

1.title: Big Deal
1.plot: The cowboys get a million-dollar business opportunity, but only if they can come up with big cash. Booger gives Matthew his first pony, but when Jaclyn misses it she questions if her job is keeping her from her family. Cody takes on the Cattlemen's Association.

2.title: New Sheriff in Town
2.plot: A routine cattle wrangle suddenly heads south. Bubba invests in a starter herd for Andie's Cowgirl College Fund, while Kaley thinks about getting a job. Jaclyn rushes to plan Matthew's birthday party and gets some bad news. Cody makes an impact with a local rancher's autistic son.

3.title: A New Chapter
3.plot: It's man vs machine in a wild episode. Bubba's barn-raising plans backfire when his bulldozer breaks a pipeline, shooting water sky-high. Jaclyn fears she might get fired after asking to go part-time. Cody starts writing a book while the guys scramble to finish the barn in time for their new herd.

4.title: Keep On Chuckin'
4.plot: It's a Cowboy Way road trip! The guys head north to enter a dangerous high-stakes, chuck wagon race. Do they have what it takes to win? Back home, the wives must handle a surprise cattle shipment and discover one heifer has an infection that could threaten the entire herd.

5.title: Getting Schooled
5.plot: Booger goes back to school on The Cowboy Way! But before he can hit auctioneering class, the guys get into hot water when their herd escapes into a neighbor's field. And plunging cattle prices leads to a tough talk between the cowboys and their million-dollar business partner.

6.title: Keep On Truckin'
6.plot: The boys head west to Louisiana on The Cowboy Way. They hit the road in search of the perfect bull, but several unexpected pit stops and Booger's backseat antics make it a road trip to remember. Back home Jaclyn and Kaley try a hot yoga class and Misty takes a shine to modeling.

7.title: Cajun Persuasion
7.plot: On The Cowboy Way, the guys jump into air boats and learn how to herd cattle Louisiana-style, dodging gators! Are Bubba and Booger... related? Cody discovers the guys share a family name. Booger coaches Matthew's tee-ball team. The whole gang gets together for a family day at the lake.

8.title: Get Off My Lawn!
8.plot: The cowboys get a million-dollar business opportunity, but only if they can come up with big cash. Booger gives Matthew his first pony, but when Jaclyn misses it she questions if her job is keeping her from her family. Cody takes on the Cattlemen's Association.

9.title: Done Deal
9.plot: On this episode of The Cowboy Way, it's delivery day for the herd...and the big final paycheck! Cody is nervous about a shipping delay of his new book. Booger and Jaclyn plan a surprise for Booger's grandmother. The Cattlemen's Association hosts a ball with a special honor for the guys.

imdb.plot outline: INSP's original series The Cowboy Way sets the stage for real-life cowboy adventures. This one-hour series follows three modern-day cowboys - Bubba, Cody, and Booger - as they build their business in south Alabama herding cattle, breaking horses and tilling fields. The Old West meets the Deep South with these buddies who live by a Cowboy Code that is as important to them today as it was to those who first tamed the Old West. They work hard, play hard and depend on each other. They love their families and the rugged life they've chosen. Their days may not be easy, but these three friends wouldn't have it any other way.
